<subSubSection id="34AD6563067AF15D304EEF84B772EB17" pageId="1" pageNumber="130" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="7C0836E8067AF15D304EEF84B772EB17" blockId="1.[811,1454,1463,1903]" pageId="1" pageNumber="130">
<emphasis id="4EC3EAFA067AF15D304EEF84B1D6E9B7" bold="true" box="[813,925,1463,1487]" pageId="1" pageNumber="130">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="BBB74D6B067AF15D30CBEF8BB73BE9B7" authority="(Song &amp; Li, 2010)" authorityName="Tanasevitch" authorityYear="2019" baseAuthorityName="Song &amp; Li" baseAuthorityYear="2010" box="[936,1392,1463,1487]" class="Arachnida" family="Linyphiidae" genus="Vietnagone" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="130" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rugulosa" status="new combination">
<emphasis id="4EC3EAFA067AF15D30CBEF8BB6C4E9B7" box="[936,1167,1463,1487]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="130">Vietnagone rugulosa</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="18264B19067AF15D37C2EF84B723E9B7" author="Song YJ &amp; Li SQ" box="[1185,1384,1463,1487]" firstAuthor="Song" journalOrPublisher="Acta Zootaxonomica Sinica" pageId="1" pageNumber="130" pagination="703 - 715" part="35" refId="ref3061" refString="Song YJ &amp; Li SQ (2010) Three new record genera and three new species of Erigoninae from China (Araneae, Linyphiidae). Acta Zootaxonomica Sinica, 35: 703 - 715." title="Three new record genera and three new species of Erigoninae from China (Araneae, Linyphiidae)" type="journal article" year="2010">Song &amp; Li, 2010</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel id="55F05781067AF15D361DEF84B1FBE997" pageId="1" pageNumber="130" rank="species">new combination</taxonomicNameLabel>
was originally described in 
<taxonomicName id="BBB74D6B067AF15D37AEEFE4B129EA77" authority="Menge, 1868" authorityName="Menge" authorityYear="1868" class="Arachnida" family="Linyphiidae" genus="Gongylidium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="130" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="4EC3EAFA067AF15D37AEEFE4B71DE997" box="[1229,1366,1495,1519]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="130">Gongylidium</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="18264B19067AF15D363FEFE4B129EA77" author="Menge A" firstAuthor="Menge" journalOrPublisher="Schriften der Naturforschenden Gesellschaft in Danzig (N. F.)" pageId="1" pageNumber="130" pagination="153 - 218" part="2" refId="ref2974" refString="Menge A (1868) Preussische Spinnen. II. Abtheilung. Schriften der Naturforschenden Gesellschaft in Danzig (N. F.) 2: 153 - 218." title="Preussische Spinnen. II. Abtheilung" type="journal article" year="1868">Menge, 1868</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, from Bome and Nyingchi counties of 
<collectingRegion id="BE73F80A067AF15D3792EFC4B762EA77" box="[1265,1321,1527,1551]" country="China" name="Xizang" pageId="1" pageNumber="130">Tibet</collectingRegion>
(
<bibRefCitation id="18264B19067AF15D3656EFC4B12EEA57" author="Song YJ &amp; Li SQ" firstAuthor="Song" journalOrPublisher="Acta Zootaxonomica Sinica" pageId="1" pageNumber="130" pagination="703 - 715" part="35" refId="ref3061" refString="Song YJ &amp; Li SQ (2010) Three new record genera and three new species of Erigoninae from China (Araneae, Linyphiidae). Acta Zootaxonomica Sinica, 35: 703 - 715." title="Three new record genera and three new species of Erigoninae from China (Araneae, Linyphiidae)" type="journal article" year="2010">Song &amp; Li, 2010</bibRefCitation>
). The structure of the palp, namely, the modified palpal tibia, the presence of a convector (in the original description referred to as “lamella”), the relatively short and looped embolus, as well as the same chaeto- and trichobothriotaxy, all support the assignment of 
<taxonomicName id="BBB74D6B067AF15D3709ECA4B1EBEAB7" authority="Song &amp; Li, 2010" authorityName="Song &amp; Li" authorityYear="2010" class="Arachnida" family="Linyphiidae" genus="Gongylidium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="130" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rugulosum">
<emphasis id="4EC3EAFA067AF15D3709ECA4B726EAD7" box="[1130,1389,1687,1711]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="130">Gongylidium rugulosum</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="18264B19067AF15D3616ECA4B1EBEAB7" author="Song YJ &amp; Li SQ" firstAuthor="Song" journalOrPublisher="Acta Zootaxonomica Sinica" pageId="1" pageNumber="130" pagination="703 - 715" part="35" refId="ref3061" refString="Song YJ &amp; Li SQ (2010) Three new record genera and three new species of Erigoninae from China (Araneae, Linyphiidae). Acta Zootaxonomica Sinica, 35: 703 - 715." title="Three new record genera and three new species of Erigoninae from China (Araneae, Linyphiidae)" type="journal article" year="2010">Song &amp; Li, 2010</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
to 
<taxonomicName id="BBB74D6B067AF15D30DCEC8BB673EAB7" authority="Tanasevitch, 2019" authorityName="Tanasevitch" authorityYear="2019" box="[959,1080,1720,1743]" class="Arachnida" family="Linyphiidae" genus="Vietnagone" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="130" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="new genus">
<emphasis id="4EC3EAFA067AF15D30DCEC8BB673EAB7" box="[959,1080,1720,1743]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="130">Vietnagone</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel id="55F05781067AF15D3725EC84B6F1EAB7" box="[1094,1210,1719,1743]" pageId="1" pageNumber="130" rank="genus">new genus</taxonomicNameLabel>
. This species is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="BBB74D6B067AF15D3029ECEBB188EA97" authority="Tanasevitch, 2019" authorityName="Tanasevitch" authorityYear="2019" box="[842,963,1751,1775]" class="Arachnida" family="Linyphiidae" genus="Vietnagone" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="130" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="silvatica" status="new species">
<emphasis id="4EC3EAFA067AF15D3029ECEBB188EA97" box="[842,963,1751,1775]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="130">V. silvatica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel id="55F05781067AF15D30B1ECE4B61CEA97" box="[978,1111,1751,1775]" pageId="1" pageNumber="130" rank="species">new species</taxonomicNameLabel>
, but differs by the shape of the palpal tibia in the male (
<figureCitation id="E48C2A6D067AF15D375FECC4B6E8EB77" box="[1084,1187,1783,1807]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="3.[113,157,1902,1924]" captionTargetBox="[115,1451,323,1886]" captionTargetId="figure-13@3.[109,1461,312,1895]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figs. 7–13. Details of palpal and epigynal structure of Vietnagone silvatica, new species. 7–10, male holotype; 12, 13, female paratype. 7, left palp, retrolateral view; 8, 9, palpal tibia, prolateral and dorsal views, respectively; 10, distal suprategular apophysis, lateral view; 11, embolic division; 12, 13, epigyne, ventral and dorsal views, respectively." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4577003" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4577003/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="130">Figs. 7–9</figureCitation>
cf. 
<figureCitation id="E48C2A6D067AF15D37B3ECC4B76CEB77" box="[1232,1319,1783,1807]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="4.[135,179,1926,1948]" captionTargetBox="[138,1474,297,1911]" captionTargetId="figure-8@4.[132,1474,283,1921]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figs. 14–20. Details of palpal and epigynal structure of Nasoonaria pseudoembolica, new species. 14–17, male holotype; 18–20, female paratype. 14, 15, right palp, retrolateral and prolateral views, respectively; 16, palpal tibia, dorsal view; 17, embolic division; 18, 19, epigyne, ventral views, different aspects; 20, epigyne, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4577005" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4577005/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="130">
Figs. 
<quantity id="BB4F9B0D067AF15D366EECC4B76CEB77" box="[1293,1319,1783,1807]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.08" metricValueMax="5.334" metricValueMin="4.826" pageId="1" pageNumber="130" unit="in" value="20.0" valueMax="21.0" valueMin="19.0">19</quantity>
</figureCitation>
–21 in 
<bibRefCitation id="18264B19067AF15D3615ECC4B1E6EB57" author="Song YJ &amp; Li SQ" firstAuthor="Song" journalOrPublisher="Acta Zootaxonomica Sinica" pageId="1" pageNumber="130" pagination="703 - 715" part="35" refId="ref3061" refString="Song YJ &amp; Li SQ (2010) Three new record genera and three new species of Erigoninae from China (Araneae, Linyphiidae). Acta Zootaxonomica Sinica, 35: 703 - 715." title="Three new record genera and three new species of Erigoninae from China (Araneae, Linyphiidae)" type="journal article" year="2010">Song &amp; Li, 2010</bibRefCitation>
), as well as by the non-projecting epigyne, the much longer copulatory ducts and their arrangement (
<figureCitation id="E48C2A6D067AF15D3615ED04B138EB17" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="3.[113,157,1902,1924]" captionTargetBox="[115,1451,323,1886]" captionTargetId="figure-13@3.[109,1461,312,1895]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figs. 7–13. Details of palpal and epigynal structure of Vietnagone silvatica, new species. 7–10, male holotype; 12, 13, female paratype. 7, left palp, retrolateral view; 8, 9, palpal tibia, prolateral and dorsal views, respectively; 10, distal suprategular apophysis, lateral view; 11, embolic division; 12, 13, epigyne, ventral and dorsal views, respectively." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4577003" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4577003/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="130">Figs. 12, 13</figureCitation>
cf. Figs. 50–54, 56 in 
<bibRefCitation id="18264B19067AF15D3713ED64B765EB17" author="Song YJ &amp; Li SQ" box="[1136,1326,1879,1903]" firstAuthor="Song" journalOrPublisher="Acta Zootaxonomica Sinica" pageId="1" pageNumber="130" pagination="703 - 715" part="35" refId="ref3061" refString="Song YJ &amp; Li SQ (2010) Three new record genera and three new species of Erigoninae from China (Araneae, Linyphiidae). Acta Zootaxonomica Sinica, 35: 703 - 715." title="Three new record genera and three new species of Erigoninae from China (Araneae, Linyphiidae)" type="journal article" year="2010">Song &amp; Li, 2010</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="34AD6563067AF15D304EEDA4B13FEBB7" pageId="1" pageNumber="130" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="7C0836E8067AF15D304EEDA4B13FEBB7" blockId="1.[813,1451,1943,1999]" pageId="1" pageNumber="130">
<emphasis id="4EC3EAFA067AF15D304EEDA4B1F4EBD7" bold="true" box="[813,959,1943,1967]" pageId="1" pageNumber="130">Distribution.</emphasis>
Known from southeastern 
<collectingRegion id="BE73F80A067AF15D3784EDA4B754EBD7" box="[1255,1311,1943,1967]" country="China" name="Xizang" pageId="1" pageNumber="130">Tibet</collectingRegion>
(
<bibRefCitation id="18264B19067AF15D364CEDA4B123EBB7" author="Song YJ &amp; Li SQ" firstAuthor="Song" journalOrPublisher="Acta Zootaxonomica Sinica" pageId="1" pageNumber="130" pagination="703 - 715" part="35" refId="ref3061" refString="Song YJ &amp; Li SQ (2010) Three new record genera and three new species of Erigoninae from China (Araneae, Linyphiidae). Acta Zootaxonomica Sinica, 35: 703 - 715." title="Three new record genera and three new species of Erigoninae from China (Araneae, Linyphiidae)" type="journal article" year="2010">Song &amp; Li, 2010</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
